Detailed Description

An interface the map_variables element.

Member Data Documentation

attribute CellMLVariable cellml_api::MapVariables::firstVariable

The first variable. If this has already been added to a Connection, it must refer to the same Component as firstComponent(if it is set). If the component in the MapComponents has not been set, this implicitly sets it. If this has not been added to the Connection, the checks are performed at the time it is added.

attribute CellMLAttributeString cellml_api::MapVariables::firstVariableName

The name of the first variable. The variable name is interpreted only in the context of MapComponents, and so may only be read or set after the MapVariables is added to a Connection, and the Connection has in turn been added to a model. It also requires that the component name has already been set. CellMLException if the MapVariables has not been added to a Connection, or the Connection has not been added to the Model.

attribute CellMLVariable cellml_api::MapVariables::secondVariable

The second variable. If this has already been added to a Connection, it must refer to the same Component as secondComponent(if it is set). If the component in the MapComponents has not been set, this implicitly sets it. If this has not been added to the Connection, the checks are performed at the time it is added.

attribute CellMLAttributeString cellml_api::MapVariables::secondVariableName

The name of the second variable. The variable name is interpreted only in the context of MapComponents, and so may only be read or set after the MapVariables is added to a Connection, and the Connection has in turn been added to a model. It also requires that the component name has already been set. CellMLException if the MapVariables has not been added to a Connection, or the Connection has not been added to the Model.
